2), pp. 167-185; Nyssen, J., Poesen, J., Moeyersons, J., Deckers, J., Mitiku,, H., Processes and rates of rock fragment displacement on cliffs and scree slopes in an amba landscape, Ethiopia (2006) Geomorphology, 81, pp. 265-275; Nyssen, J., Nigussie Haregeweyn, Descheemaeker, K., Desta Gebremichael, Vancampenhout, K., Poesen, K., Mitiku Haile, Govers, G., Comment on ""Modelling the effect of soil and water conservation practices in Tigray, Ethiopia"" (2006) Agric. Ecosyst. Environ., 114, pp. 407-411; Nyssen, J., Naudts, J., De Geyndt, K., Mitiku, Haile, Poesen, J., Moeyersons, J., Deckers, J., in press. Soils and land use in the Tigray Highlands (Northern Ethiopia). Land Degradation and Development. doi:10.1002/ldr.840Russo, A., Fantozzi, P.L., Solomon, T., Getaneh, A., Neri, C., Russo, F., Asfwossen, A., Valera, P., (1996) Geological Map of the Mekelle Outlier (Western Sheet), Italian Cooperation, , Addis Ababa University, Addis Ababa; Schroder, J.F., Mass movement on Nyika Plateau, Malawi (1976) Z. Geomorphol., 20, pp. 56-77. , N.F; Stengel, I., Fossil landslides in the Schwarzrand, Huib and Huns escarpment areas - a contribution to the Quaternary morphostratigraphy of Southern Namibia (2001) Palaeoecol. Afr surround. Isl., 27, pp. 221-238; Tesfaye,, C., Gebretsadik,, E., (1982) Hydrogeology of the Mekelle Area, , Ministry of Mines and Energy, Addis Ababa 50 p; Thomas, M.F., (1996) Geomorphology in the Tropics, , John Wiley and Sons, Chichester; Twidale, C.R., (1982) Granite Landforms, , Elsevier, Amsterdam 372 p; Vandecasteele, I., 2007. Hydrogeological investigation in the area of May Zegzeg, near to Hagere Selam (Northern Tigray, Ethiopia). MSc-thesis, Department of Geology, Ghent University, Belgium, 142 pVan de Wauw, J., Baert, G., Moeyersons, J., Nyssen, J., De Geyndt, K., Nurhussein, T., Amanuel, Z., Deckers, J., Soil-Landscape Relationships in the Basalt-Dominated Highlands of Tigray (2008) Ethiopia, 75, pp. 117-127; Woldearegay, K., Schubert, W., Klima, 